      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is not good.\n\nIt takes an image with (old) go1.11, copies \u0027results\u0027 source code (and only it) from the local checkout, then asks \u0027go\u0027 tool inside the container to fetch all dependencies from the internet, at whatever state they happened to be at the time (no version pinning). In particular, this fetches go.chromium.org/luci/* from internet, not local checkout. So if you happen to work on some dependency of results/* which is outside of results/* directory tree, it will not pick it up.\n\nThere\u0027s absolutely no reason to use \"golang\" image, we already have local go building environment that produces reproducible builds.\n\nWe should build the server binary locally, outside the container, using all source code we already have there, and then just copy the final binary into a tiny image.\n\nSee for example: \nhttps://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/infra/+/refs/heads/master/go/src/infra/appengine/qscheduler-swarming/cmd/qscheduler-swarming/Dockerfile\nhttps://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/infra/+/refs/heads/master/go/src/infra/appengine/qscheduler-swarming/Makefile?autodive\u003d0#55\n\nIt uses Cloud Build, but same would work with \"docker build\":\n\n```\nFROM gcr.io/distroless/static:latest\nCOPY bin/frontend ./frontend\nUSER nobody\nENTRYPOINT [\"./frontend\"]\n```\n\n$ CGO_ENABLED\u003d0 GOOS\u003dlinux GOARCH\u003damd64 go build -o bin/frontend ./app/frontend\n$ docker build .",
